# Cloudflare Pages reads this file automatically at deploy time — no build
# step or extra configuration needed. It fixes 3 of the 7 issues flagged in
# your Screaming Frog crawl (missing X-Frame-Options, missing CSP, missing
# HSTS), since those can only be set as real HTTP response headers, not as
# <meta> tags in the HTML.
#
# Reference: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/

/*
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://www.googletagmanager.com https://www.google-analytics.com https://cdn.jsdelivr.net; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' data: https:; connect-src 'self' https://*.supabase.co https://www.google-analytics.com https://www.googletagmanager.com; frame-ancestors 'self'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'

# Notes:
# - 'unsafe-inline' is required for script-src/style-src because this site
#   intentionally ships as a single self-contained HTML file (inline <style>
#   and inline <script>, no build step). If the CSS/JS are ever split into
#   external files with a build step, this can be tightened to a nonce- or
#   hash-based policy instead — genuinely stricter, but not a drop-in change.
# - connect-src whitelists your Supabase project and Google Analytics/Tag
#   Manager endpoints, since the contact form and newsletter signup call
#   Supabase directly from the browser, and gtag.js reports back to GA.
